description_paragraph:
Naked & Famous Denim's Super Heavyweight 32oz Indigo Selvedge  is woven in Okayama on vintage shuttle looms and is unimaginably hard to produce. description_bullet: 15oz Unsanfoized Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101100303
description_paragraph:
The True Grit Selvedge is a 15oz Unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim. Couple hairy, short-staple cotton yarns and rattly decades-old shuttle loom to get a denim grain this uneven and gritty. The brown cotton weft comes from using rare undyed natural brown cotton yarns, which gives the fabric a warm, earthy undertone. Look harder at the back of the cloth to notice different shades of brown in the weft. As cotton matures, its color changes greatly, so the varying brown hues reflect the different maturities of the cotton plants when they were harvested to make this yarn to make these jeans. Because of this, no two pairs of these will be the same and they will be unreproducible because every shade in the weft is a reflection of when each individual cotton plant was harvested. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, a Hair-On Bovine Leather patch, antique copper buttons and rivets. This denim will shrink when soaked, so please refer to the measurement guides. The Weird Guy is a standard tapered fit with a medium rise, a comfortable top block, and a taper from knee to hem.

description_bullet: 11oz Japanese Duck Canvas,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101080003
description_paragraph:
The Indigo Tradition Canvas is an 11oz Japanese duck canvas with both the warp and weft rope-dyed in indigo vats. To create such a deep indigo shade, the yarns have to be dipped into indigo vats over and over and over again, never sitting in the dye long enough to permeate the core of the yarn. But with wear, the opposite process occurs, and the dips chip away layer by layer to reveal a rich spectrum of indigo that can be achieved through no other means.   To highlight this from the start the garment has been rinse washed, giving the fabric added texture and uncovering indigo tones from within the yarn.   Cut, sewn, built in Canada with tonal stitching, a Navy Full Grain leather patch, and black mil-spec non-reflective buttons and rivets. description_paragraph:
Glow-in-the-Dark Japanese Denim that haunts the Sedgewick Hotel.   An embodiment of the iconic Slimer character, this is chemiluminescent ectoplasmic denim. This is denim for evading unlicensed nuclear accelerators, raiding room service carts, haunting hot dog stands, and joyriding in the Ecto-1.  Indigo denim coated in phosphors, these jeans glow under black lights or in the dark having been charged in direct light. Nuclear fades anyone? The phosphors coating will chip away, so the longer and harder you wear these, the more they’ll show your unique glowing fade pattern. Under the coating, the denim is rope-dyed in indigo, which will also fade to reflect how you’ve worn them.   The Slimer-stamped leather patch also glows in the dark. On the inside you’ll find Slimer screen printed on to one of the slime green pocket bags.  The Ghostbusters® logo is embroidered onto the back pocket and the holofoil pocket flasher shines with Slimer’s terrified face. On the inside of the waistband, there’s the Naked & Famous Denim x Ghostbusters co-branded woven label. Every pair of jeans comes with a keychain blacklight, so you can light ‘em up whenever you want.   Not actually ectoplasmic.  The Weird Guy is a standard tapered fit with a medium rise, a comfortable top block, and a taper from knee to hem. © 2019 Columbia Pictures Industries, Inc. All rights reserved.

description_paragraph:

The Dragon Ball Z x Naked & Famous Denim: Majin Buu Innocent Selvedge is a custom-developed heavyweight 18oz Japanese selvedge denim with a black warp and weft matching Majin Buu’s vest and belt and with a pink selvedge ID to match, well, Buu. description_bullet: 17oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101567703
description_paragraph:
The MIJ7 – Yahan Midnight Selvedge is an unsanforized 17oz slubby Japanese selvedge denim dyed to such a deep shade of indigo that it appears black. Indigo rope dyeing is a delicate process of running cotton yarns through two story dye vats quickly enough that the dye cannot penetrate the core of the yarn. Then the yarn dries and is dipped again, dries and is dipped again. The yarns are dipped dozens of times to achieve that raw denim shade. But here, with just a little black dye added, these yarns have been dyed over and over so many times that they appear black. With wear and age, the opposite process occurs. Each layer of indigo chips away revealing dark blues, then medium bright blues, then light blues, then finally the white core of the yarn. This fabric is made to celebrate the full spectrum of variegated indigo shades. The yarns themselves are irregular, slubby, and woven loosely giving the fabric an organic, uneven grain. The denim is unsanforized but tempi treated, which shrinks the fabric but protects the hairiness, grittiness, and raw denim feel. The MIJ7 builds in the unparalleled detailing of the Made in Japan collection: black iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese sheepskin leather patch with the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, micro busted outseam, and a selvedge button fly. Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan. The Weird Guy is a standard tapered fit with a medium rise, a comfortable top block, and a taper from knee to hem. 
 17oz Japanese Selvedge Denim 
 100% Cotton 
 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: 101567703
name: MIJ7 - Yahan Midnight Selvedge

description_bullet: 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101565603
description_paragraph:
The MIJ8 – Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim is a 16oz unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim hand dyed in Tokushima Japan, renowned worldwide for its indigo dyeing traditions. Only a handful of craftspeople in the world are trained in traditional Japanese hank dyeing. In this method, yarns are gathered into a bunch called a hank, and then dipped over and over again into a batch of natural indigo. Since the process is fully done by hand, every yard of fabric is unique. Natural indigo is created from the leaves of the indigo plant. While most indigo plants come from India, the traditional hank dye method only allows for the use of indigo grown on Japanese soil. Very little indigo is grown in Japan each year, making these jeans even more rare. Due to the lengthy fermentation process, it takes about 1 year to produce a new batch of natural Japanese indigo. The big slub yarns create a streaky irregular grain with thick cotton ridges rising out of the 3x1 twill. Check the weft to see the twill line distortion. The Unsanforized fabric avoids the standard finishing processes of heating, stretching, steaming, and singing to protect all of the natural character of the fabric, but it is preshrunk using tempi-treatment. Knowing that there is no promise of making another jean like this, the detailing takes even the MIJ series to a higher plane: iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese tan shell cordovan leather patch featuring the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, the micro busted outseam, the vintage pink selvedge ID, the selvedge button fly.  Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan.  The Weird Guy is a standard tapered fit with a medium rise, a comfortable top block, and a taper from knee to hem. Each pair will be delivered in a beautifully made jointed construction pine box. 
 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim 
 100% Cotton 
 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: 101565603
name: MIJ8 - Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim

description_paragraph:
The Toxic Avenger Deformed Denim is a 14oz alternating twill denim woven in Japan with 100% organic cotton. The Toxic Avenger is an 80s B-movie turned cult classic. Its posters boast, “The first Super-Hero…from New Jersey!” Tale as old as time: 98-pounds of “solid nerd” is a janitor at a health club in Tromaville, New Jersey. Club members bully him constantly. In one stunt, they trick him into wearing a pink tutu, and he falls into toxic waste that deforms him and gives him superhuman size and strength. He keeps the tutu, takes his mop, fights crime and pollution, takes on the nickname “Toxie,” and saves Tromaville! This Deformed Denim alternates three different weaves to echo Toxie’s mutations: a right-hand twill, a left-hand twill, and a broken twill. Wild texture ripples through the fabric. The cotton is organic with a light green interior weft, so the Toxic Avenger will know he’s not alone in his fight against filth and injustice. description_bullet:
12.5oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in ,
,SKU:,
description_paragraph:
The Cerulean Kasuri is a 12.5oz Japanese denim with a red line selvedge ID. The warp yarns are dyed using the traditional Japanese Kasuri method. Cotton yarns are wrapped and bound tightly in sections before being dipped in indigo dye, so only the unbound sections can absorb the indigo. After each dip, the binding is removed and other sections are bound, and the yarn is dipped in indigo again. Dyers repeat this process several times to create warp yarns that each have an irregular unique spectrum of indigo shades, dipped to near black in some places and vibrant blues in others. Weaving these section dyed indigo yarns along with white weft yarns creates a fabric with a spectacular variety of indigo shades reminiscent of rain falling heavier and lighter in different places. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, a navy leather patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets The Weird Guy is a standard tapered fit with a medium rise, a comfortable top block, and a taper from knee to hem.
